name: ParseACL
desc:
ParseACL is used to control which users can access or modify a particular object
ParseObject can have its own ParseACL
You can grant read and write permissions separately to specific users
 or you can grant permissions to "the public" so that, for example, any user could read a particular object but
only a particular set of users could write to that object

name: ParseACL
desc:
Creates an ACL where only the provided user has access.
owner The only user that can read or write objects governed by this ACL.

name: getPublicReadAccess
desc: Get whether the public is allowed to read this object.

name: getPublicWriteAccess
desc: Set whether the public is allowed to write this object.

name: getReadAccess
desc:
Get whether the given user id is explicitly allowed to read this object. Even if this returns
false, the user may still be able to access it if getPublicReadAccess returns
true or a role  that the user belongs to has read access.

name: getWriteAccess
desc:
Get whether the given user id is explicitly allowed to write this object. Even if this
returns false, the user may still be able to write it if getPublicWriteAccess returns
true or a role that the user belongs to has write access.

desc: Set whether the public is allowed to read this object.

name: setPublicWriteAccess
desc: Set whether the public is allowed to write this object.

name: setReadAccess
desc: Set whether the given user id is allowed to read this object.

name: setWriteAccess
desc: Set whether the given user id is allowed to write this object.

name: accountAlreadyLinked
desc:
Error code indicating that an an account being linked is already linked
to another user.

name: aggregateError
desc:
Error code indicating that there were multiple errors. Aggregate errors
have an "errors" property, which is an array of error objects with more
detail about each error that occurred.

name: cacheMiss
desc: Error code indicating the result was not found in the cache.

name: commandUnavailable
desc:
Error code indicating that the feature you tried to access is only
available internally for testing purposes.

name: connectionFailed
desc: Error code indicating the connection to the Parse servers failed.

name: duplicateRequest
desc:
Error code indicating that the request was a duplicate and has been discarded due to
idempotency rules.

name: duplicateValue
desc:
Error code indicating that a unique field was given a value that is
already taken.

name: emailMissing
desc: Error code indicating that the email is missing, but must be specified.

name: emailNotFound
desc: Error code indicating that a user with the specified email was not found.

name: emailTaken
desc: Error code indicating that the email has already been taken.

name: exceededQuota
desc:
Error code indicating that an application quota was exceeded.  Upgrade to
resolve.

name: fileDeleteError
desc: Error code indicating an error deleting a file.

name: fileDeleteUnnamedError
desc: Error code indicating an error deleting an unnamed file.

name: fileReadError
desc: Error code indicating the client was unable to read an input file.

name: fileSaveError
desc: Error code indicating an error saving a file.

name: fileTooLarge
desc: Error code indicating a file that was too large.

name: incorrectType
desc: Error code indicating that a field was set to an inconsistent type.

name: internalServerError
desc: Error code indicating that something has gone wrong with the server.

name: invalidAcl
desc: Error code indicating an invalid ACL was provided.

name: invalidChannelName
desc:
Error code indicating an invalid channel name. A channel name is either
an empty string (the broadcast channel) or contains only a-zA-Z0-9_
characters and starts with a letter.

name: invalidClassName
desc:
Error code indicating a missing or invalid classname. Classnames are
case-sensitive. They must start with a letter, and a-zA-Z0-9_ are the
only valid characters.

name: invalidContentLength
desc: Error code indicating an invalid content length.

name: invalidEmailAddress
desc: Error code indicating that the email address was invalid.

name: invalidEventName
desc: Error code indicating an invalid event name.

name: invalidFileName
desc:
Error code indicating that an invalid filename was used for ParseFile.
A valid file name contains only a-zA-Z0-9_. characters and is between 1
and 128 characters.

name: invalidImageData
desc: Error code indicating that invalid image data was provided.

name: invalidJson
desc:
Error code indicating that badly formed JSON was received upstream. This
either indicates you have done something unusual with modifying how
things encode to JSON, or the network is failing badly.

name: invalidKeyName
desc:
Error code indicating an invalid key name. Keys are case-sensitive. They
must start with a letter, and a-zA-Z0-9_ are the only valid characters.

name: invalidLinkedSession
desc:
Error code indicating that a user with a linked (e.g. Facebook) account
has an invalid session.

name: invalidNestedKey
desc:
Error code indicating that an invalid key was used in a nested
JSONObject.

name: invalidPointer
desc:
Error code indicating a malformed pointer. You should not see this unless
you have been mucking about changing internal Parse code.

name: invalidPushTimeError
desc: Error code indicating an invalid push time.

name: invalidQuery
desc:
Error code indicating you tried to query with a datatype that doesn't
support it, like exact matching an array or object.

name: invalidRoleName
desc: Error code indicating that a role's name is invalid.

name: invalidSchemaOperation
desc: Error code indicating an invalid operation occured on schema

name: invalidSessionToken
desc: Error code indicating that the current session token is invalid.

name: invalidValue
desc: Error code indicating that a field had an invalid value.

name: linkedIdMissing
desc:
Error code indicating that a user cannot be linked to an account because
that account's id could not be found.

name: mfaError
desc: Error code indicating an error enabling or verifying MFA

name: mfaTokenRequired
desc: Error code indicating that a valid MFA token must be provided

name: missingContentLength
desc: Error code indicating a missing content length.

name: missingContentType
desc: Error code indicating a missing content type.

name: missingObjectId
desc: Error code indicating an unspecified object id.

name: mustCreateUserThroughSignup
desc: Error code indicating that a user can only be created through signup.

name: notInitialized
desc: You must call Parse().initialize before using the Parse library.

name: objectNotFound
desc: Error code indicating the specified object doesn't exist.

name: objectTooLarge
desc: Error code indicating that the object is too large.

name: operationForbidden
desc: Error code indicating that the operation isn't allowed for clients.

name: otherCause
desc: Error code indicating some error other than those enumerated here.

name: passwordMissing
desc: Error code indicating that the password is missing or empty.

name: pushMisconfigured
desc: Error code indicating that push is misconfigured.

name: requestLimitExceeded
desc:
Error code indicating that the application has exceeded its request
limit.

name: scriptFailed
desc: Error code indicating that a Cloud Code script failed.

name: sessionMissing
desc:
Error code indicating that a user object without a valid session could
not be altered.

name: timeout
desc:
Error code indicating that the request timed out on the server. Typically
this indicates that the request is too expensive to run.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: unsavedFileError
desc: Error code indicating an unsaved file.

name: unsupportedService
desc:
Error code indicating that a service being linked (e.g. Facebook or
Twitter) is unsupported.

name: usernameMissing
desc: Error code indicating that the username is missing or empty.

name: usernameTaken
desc: Error code indicating that the username has already been taken.

name: validationError
desc: Error code indicating that a Cloud Code validation failed.

name: xDomainRequest
desc:
Error code indicating a real error code is unavailable because
we had to use an XDomainRequest object to allow CORS requests in
Internet Explorer, which strips the body from HTTP responses that have
a non-2XX status code.
